    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "No worries, I won't goblin-ize the explanation this time. To rewrite a passive sentence to active, follow these simple steps: \n\n1. Identify the passive verb form (the verb \"to be\" + past participle).\n2. Determine the doer of the action (the agent, if you will).\n3. Replace the passive verb form with the active verb form, using the doer as the subject.\n\nFor example, in the sentence \"The ball was thrown by John,\" the doer is John. To rewrite it in active voice, you would change the sentence to: \"John threw the ball.\" \n\nAnother common way to rewrite passive sentences is to use the phrase \"by [agent]\" or \"performed by [agent]\" to make it clear who did the action. For instance: \"The ball was thrown by John\" becomes \"The ball was thrown by John, who is a skilled athlete.\"",
      "source": "target",
